answers.answer: Did you check your blood pressure? That can be a sign of high blood pressure. Although its too early to be preeclampsia, you can still have HP
Yes, blood pressure is normal. I have no other complaints besides muscle tension in my neck and back of my head...

question: I am not sure if this is posted in the correct area as I am only 7 weeks pregnant. Last Wednesday I noticed my ears ringing at night when I laid down to take a nap or go to sleep at night. Doctors dont seem concerned and have no resolution and it is driving me crazy. It is to the point where I have to sleep with soft music playing which I hate...Is this a normal part of early pregnancy? Help anyone!?!
title: Ringing Ears
